1
00:00:03,128 --> 00:00:05,547
[theme song playing]

2
00:01:22,374 --> 00:01:28,297
TACTICS

3
00:01:28,474 --> 00:01:29,502
[car engine idling]

4
00:01:29,673 --> 00:01:33,385
DECEMBER 20, 11:50 A.M.

5
00:01:45,188 --> 00:01:46,815
-[Raye Penber] You there?
-Yeah?

6
00:01:47,232 --> 00:01:50,527
Listen carefully, I came to Japan
as a part of a secret investigation,

7
00:01:50,611 --> 00:01:52,362
so the local police can't find out that…

8
00:01:52,487 --> 00:01:54,239
Um… That I'm…

9
00:01:55,657 --> 00:01:56,700
I understand.

10
00:01:56,867 --> 00:01:58,869
I promise, I won't tell anyone
that I met you.

11
00:01:59,036 --> 00:02:01,496
And of course, that includes my father.

12
00:02:02,247 --> 00:02:04,124
[Penber] Well then… Please excuse me.

13
00:02:07,210 --> 00:02:08,712
[Light] It's just as I thought.

14
00:02:09,338 --> 00:02:11,381
Anyway, I don't want the police to know

15
00:02:11,506 --> 00:02:14,719
that I've come into contact
with an FBI agent either.

16
00:02:15,442 --> 00:02:18,430
If my father ever found out,
there's no doubt he'd let L know.

17
00:02:19,139 --> 00:02:21,058
It's obvious that he doesn't suspect me.

18
00:02:21,642 --> 00:02:23,018
And as for the police…

19
00:02:23,143 --> 00:02:27,230
I'm sure they'll treat this
as just another unfortunate accident.

20
00:02:39,660 --> 00:02:40,702
[door opens]

21
00:02:41,662 --> 00:02:42,704
Hey, welcome back.

22
00:02:43,330 --> 00:02:45,040
[Penber sighs] What a day.

23
00:02:46,625 --> 00:02:49,753
Raye, what's the matter?
Something happened, didn't it?

24
00:02:49,920 --> 00:02:51,797
I've never heard you sigh like that.

25
00:02:52,339 --> 00:02:53,382
Yeah.

26
00:02:53,757 --> 00:02:56,343
The bus I was on
got hijacked, if you can believe it.

27
00:02:56,593 --> 00:02:57,886
A bus-jacking?

28
00:02:58,428 --> 00:03:00,389
Some junkie robbed a bank
two days ago

29
00:03:00,472 --> 00:03:02,724
and I guess he wanted to try
taking on a bus today.

30
00:03:03,850 --> 00:03:05,936
I didn't think this kind of thing
happened here.

31
00:03:06,687 --> 00:03:09,690
So, you were already riding the bus
when the hijacker got on?

32
00:03:09,856 --> 00:03:10,774
[Penber] Yeah.

33
00:03:11,525 --> 00:03:15,320
And in the end, the guy freaked out,
jumped off the bus and got hit by a car.

34
00:03:16,780 --> 00:03:17,906
[Naomi] Did he die?

35
00:03:19,116 --> 00:03:20,659
Yeah. Probably.

36
00:03:21,034 --> 00:03:23,328
I couldn't really stick around
to see what happened to him.

37
00:03:23,412 --> 00:03:25,038
-[Naomi] You know… [sighs]
-[Penber] Hmm?

38
00:03:25,122 --> 00:03:26,289
It's a little hard to believe

39
00:03:26,373 --> 00:03:28,250
that that was all a coincidence,
don't you think?

40
00:03:28,792 --> 00:03:29,876
[Penber] What do you mean?

41
00:03:30,001 --> 00:03:30,961
[Naomi] Think about it.

42
00:03:31,044 --> 00:03:33,547
You got on that bus because
you were investigating someone, right?

43
00:03:33,714 --> 00:03:36,550
And now you're telling me
that this criminal is most likely dead.

44
00:03:36,883 --> 00:03:39,344
-Doesn’t that suggest that you--
-[Penber] That's enough.

45
00:03:39,678 --> 00:03:43,765
Look. darling, you and I know you used
to be one of the best agents in the FBI.

46
00:03:43,890 --> 00:03:46,393
But now you're my fiancée, Naomi.
We talked about this.

47
00:03:47,060 --> 00:03:49,688
You're not an agent anymore,
so just leave it alone.

48
00:03:50,147 --> 00:03:51,148
But…

49
00:03:52,315 --> 00:03:54,443
You wouldn't get involved
with the Kira case.

50
00:03:54,609 --> 00:03:56,445
And you wouldn't do anything dangerous.

51
00:03:56,653 --> 00:03:58,363
That's what you promised
when we decided

52
00:03:58,488 --> 00:04:01,074
you'd come with me,
so I could meet your parents in Japan.

53
00:04:01,283 --> 00:04:02,534
You do remember that, don't you?

54
00:04:02,909 --> 00:04:04,536
Yeah, I guess you're right.

55
00:04:04,911 --> 00:04:07,414
It's just force of habit.
Sorry about that.

56
00:04:07,914 --> 00:04:11,126
[Penber] No… I should be sorry.
Let's forget about it.

57
00:04:11,501 --> 00:04:13,795
Anyway, once we have a few kids
running around,

58
00:04:13,879 --> 00:04:17,007
you'll probably be so busy
you'll forget you were ever an agent.

59
00:04:17,090 --> 00:04:19,593
Your mind will be occupied
with better things too.

60
00:04:19,895 --> 00:04:20,816
[gasps]

61
00:04:21,052 --> 00:04:21,970
More importantly,

62
00:04:22,095 --> 00:04:24,514
tell me how I can convince your dad
I'm worthy of his daughter.

63
00:04:24,639 --> 00:04:27,017
Kira doesn't scare me
half as much as he does.

64
00:04:27,184 --> 00:04:28,143
[Naomi chuckles]

65
00:04:29,227 --> 00:04:30,729
[Ryuk] Oh, let me guess.

66
00:04:30,929 --> 00:04:33,815
You're about to write down
the name of that agent, aren't you?

67
00:04:33,899 --> 00:04:35,567
-The one from the bus.
-Not yet.

68
00:04:36,193 --> 00:04:38,737
I'm gonna wait one week
before writing his name.

69
00:04:39,112 --> 00:04:40,822
If he dies right after meeting me,

70
00:04:40,947 --> 00:04:42,491
I'll only draw attention to myself.

71
00:04:42,616 --> 00:04:43,825
I'll write his name in here

72
00:04:43,992 --> 00:04:46,912
once I've given him time to investigate
more people with ties to the police.

73
00:04:47,037 --> 00:04:48,497
It'll be less obvious that way.

74
00:04:48,622 --> 00:04:49,790
In the meantime,

75
00:04:49,873 --> 00:04:52,209
I think I'll use some of these inmates
I've been keeping alive

76
00:04:52,292 --> 00:04:54,169
to play around with L a little more.

77
00:04:54,503 --> 00:04:55,462
[beeping]

78
00:04:55,545 --> 00:04:56,713
-[Watari] L.
-[L] Hmm?

79
00:04:57,756 --> 00:04:58,799
Another victim.

80
00:04:58,924 --> 00:05:01,551
This one left
what appears to be a suicide note.

81
00:05:01,968 --> 00:05:03,345
[L] Please, send it to me.

82
00:05:03,689 --> 00:05:04,835
[computer beeps]

83
00:05:07,265 --> 00:05:08,767
"Gods of Death."

84
00:05:08,934 --> 00:05:10,477
"L, do you know?"

85
00:05:10,769 --> 00:05:12,604
"Gods of Death"?

86
00:05:14,272 --> 00:05:17,025
Is he trying to tell us
that Gods of Death exist?

87
00:05:17,859 --> 00:05:18,819
Listen, Watari.

88
00:05:18,944 --> 00:05:21,446
Tell the police to monitor
prison populations closely

89
00:05:21,530 --> 00:05:22,656
for the next few days.

90
00:05:23,532 --> 00:05:27,077
Kira may use other suicide notes
to communicate with us.

91
00:05:27,285 --> 00:05:28,370
[Watari] Understood.

92
00:05:31,081 --> 00:05:33,375
DECEMBER 27, 3:00 P.M.

93
00:05:37,629 --> 00:05:39,714
[Ryuk] This place is crawling with humans.

94
00:05:40,006 --> 00:05:41,675
Are you gonna do it here?

95
00:05:42,008 --> 00:05:44,302
Let's just say
you're about to see the results

96
00:05:44,386 --> 00:05:47,305
of all the research and experiments
I've been doing over the last few days.

97
00:05:47,597 --> 00:05:48,515
[Ryuk] "Experiments"?

98
00:05:48,765 --> 00:05:49,641
Yeah.

99
00:05:49,808 --> 00:05:52,269
I've been using known criminals
who live in this part of town

100
00:05:52,352 --> 00:05:53,812
to test out different killing methods

101
00:05:53,937 --> 00:05:55,772
and I've learned a lot
about the Death Note.

102
00:05:56,231 --> 00:05:58,420
ACCIDENTAL DEATH, DECEMBER 26, 8:30 PM
DIES AFTER GETTING HIT BY A CAR

103
00:05:58,525 --> 00:06:00,735
For example, if I write a cause of death
and the circumstances leading up to it,

104
00:06:00,819 --> 00:06:02,320
I can add a name afterwards
and it'll still happen.

105
00:06:02,404 --> 00:06:03,280
SHO HANEKURODA

106
00:06:03,905 --> 00:06:06,950
[Ryuk] Oh… even I didn't know that one.

107
00:06:07,993 --> 00:06:09,035
He's here.

108
00:06:10,036 --> 00:06:11,162
Right on time.

109
00:06:16,376 --> 00:06:17,460
Mr. Raye Penber.

110
00:06:18,920 --> 00:06:20,922
Turn around and you're dead.

111
00:06:21,756 --> 00:06:23,925
-I am Kira.
-[gasps]

112
00:06:25,677 --> 00:06:28,555
That's right. Don't turn around
or put your hands in your pockets.

113
00:06:28,722 --> 00:06:30,307
I won't hesitate to kill you here.

114
00:06:30,599 --> 00:06:32,851
[Penber] It-- It couldn't be…

115
00:06:33,268 --> 00:06:34,269
This voice…

116
00:06:34,436 --> 00:06:35,562
I've heard it somewhere.

117
00:06:36,271 --> 00:06:38,899
But first, I'm gonna prove to you
that I am Kira.

118
00:06:39,232 --> 00:06:42,068
Do you see the man
working over there at the coffee shop?

119
00:06:42,777 --> 00:06:46,448
That's right. The one sweeping the floor.
I'm gonna kill him just for you.

120
00:06:46,656 --> 00:06:48,241
But-- But… how?

121
00:06:48,366 --> 00:06:49,492
Don't do it!

122
00:06:50,160 --> 00:06:52,287
[gasping, grunting]

123
00:06:54,039 --> 00:06:54,915
[gasps]

124
00:06:54,998 --> 00:06:57,167
I'm afraid I had no choice
but to kill him.

125
00:06:57,292 --> 00:06:59,377
I figured if I didn't kill
at least one person,

126
00:06:59,502 --> 00:07:00,837
you wouldn't believe me.

127
00:07:00,921 --> 00:07:04,215
Although that man has been repeatedly
charged with sexual assault,

128
00:07:04,299 --> 00:07:07,802
he's managed to avoid conviction
every time due to lack of evidence.

129
00:07:08,094 --> 00:07:11,222
He was a menace to society.
He got what he deserved.

130
00:07:11,765 --> 00:07:15,226
I can only assume
that L has already informed you of this.

131
00:07:15,310 --> 00:07:17,437
I can't kill someone who I haven't seen.

132
00:07:17,520 --> 00:07:18,730
I have to know their face.

133
00:07:18,855 --> 00:07:20,357
Which means, of course,

134
00:07:20,523 --> 00:07:24,027
I can easily kill all these people
right now, if I wanted to.

135
00:07:24,235 --> 00:07:26,071
Go ahead and choose someone
if you want.

136
00:07:26,279 --> 00:07:28,795
[Penber] D-- Don't do it. I believe you.
You're Kira.

137
00:07:30,951 --> 00:07:33,078
I'm sure you care more
about your loved ones

138
00:07:33,244 --> 00:07:34,621
than any of these people here.

139
00:07:34,704 --> 00:07:36,873
Imagine how you'd feel
if one of them was killed

140
00:07:37,040 --> 00:07:39,000
just because you refused to cooperate.

141
00:07:39,084 --> 00:07:42,879
I think you should consider them
the real hostages at the moment.

142
00:07:43,755 --> 00:07:45,215
How do you know about her?

143
00:07:45,642 --> 00:07:46,672
[chuckles]

144
00:07:47,217 --> 00:07:50,637
You seem surprised.
I've been investigating you.

145
00:07:51,096 --> 00:07:54,474
And if you don't do exactly as I say,
she will die.

146
00:07:54,766 --> 00:07:56,643
And so will the rest of your family.

147
00:07:56,851 --> 00:07:59,679
Including you.
And that's a promise.

148
00:07:59,980 --> 00:08:02,996
I-- I understand.
Just tell me what you need me to do.

149
00:08:03,316 --> 00:08:05,360
I see you've got your laptop with you.

150
00:08:05,610 --> 00:08:10,657
I want the files containing the identities
of all the FBI agents who came to Japan.

151
00:08:10,740 --> 00:08:14,202
[Penber] I do have my laptop with me.
It's the one I use for work.

152
00:08:14,327 --> 00:08:16,246
But I don't have the files
you're looking for.

153
00:08:16,913 --> 00:08:19,290
[Light] All right.
Then take this envelope.

154
00:08:19,509 --> 00:08:21,031
-[Penber] Huh?
-[envelope rustles]

155
00:08:21,835 --> 00:08:24,212
First, take the transceiver
out of the envelope

156
00:08:24,295 --> 00:08:26,798
and put the earpiece in
and await my instructions.

157
00:08:27,632 --> 00:08:30,335
[Penber] A transceiver.
This thing looks like a toy.

158
00:08:31,302 --> 00:08:33,596
But there'll be no record
of this transmission anywhere.

159
00:08:34,097 --> 00:08:37,267
And it allows us to converse
from a close distance, even underground.

160
00:08:37,934 --> 00:08:39,436
He really thought this through.

161
00:08:40,520 --> 00:08:43,148
[Light] All right.
Now get on the Yamanote Line.

162
00:08:43,440 --> 00:08:44,733
Inner or outer route.

163
00:08:44,816 --> 00:08:46,484
It doesn't matter
which direction you take.

164
00:08:49,279 --> 00:08:50,780
SHIBUYA - SHINAGAWA
15:10

165
00:08:50,864 --> 00:08:52,407
I will be close by at all times,

166
00:08:52,490 --> 00:08:54,284
which means I'll be watching
your every move.

167
00:08:54,409 --> 00:08:55,577
When you get on the train,

168
00:08:55,702 --> 00:08:58,496
pick a spot in front of you
and don't take your eyes of it.

169
00:08:58,705 --> 00:09:00,832
If I see you looking around,
I will kill you.

170
00:09:01,624 --> 00:09:04,919
Once you've boarded, I want you
to take the seat closest to the doors.

171
00:09:05,170 --> 00:09:07,589
If it's occupied, wait until it's free.

172
00:09:08,016 --> 00:09:09,254
[train horn blares]

173
00:09:24,355 --> 00:09:26,441
Now, I'm going to ask you something.

174
00:09:26,608 --> 00:09:29,736
If I have even the slightest suspicion
that you're not being honest,

175
00:09:29,944 --> 00:09:31,529
your girlfriend is as good as dead.

176
00:09:32,614 --> 00:09:35,408
How many FBI agents
are currently in Japan?

177
00:09:35,658 --> 00:09:38,703
Speak quietly into the transceiver
and don't make it obvious.

178
00:09:38,870 --> 00:09:40,330
I believe it's four teams.

179
00:09:40,497 --> 00:09:43,374
Three agents per team
for a total of 12.

180
00:09:43,583 --> 00:09:46,544
[Light] Okay. Now, take the papers
out of the envelope.

181
00:09:48,630 --> 00:09:49,547
Huh?

182
00:09:53,009 --> 00:09:54,677
[Penber] What… is this?

183
00:09:55,804 --> 00:09:57,806
Of those 12 agents you mentioned,

184
00:09:57,931 --> 00:09:59,933
I want you to write down
the name of your superior,

185
00:10:00,058 --> 00:10:02,102
the one who is heading up
this investigation,

186
00:10:02,310 --> 00:10:04,229
in the space at the very top of the page.

187
00:10:05,480 --> 00:10:08,380
[Penber] What is the meaning of this?
What is he after?

188
00:10:08,942 --> 00:10:10,956
Let's face it,
he hasn't really left me any choice.

189
00:10:11,444 --> 00:10:14,614
Besides, it's not like he can kill them
using just their names.

190
00:10:15,240 --> 00:10:17,534
Next, take out your laptop and turn it on.

191
00:10:17,659 --> 00:10:19,619
Any minute now your boss
is going to send you

192
00:10:19,744 --> 00:10:21,454
a message with a file attachment.

193
00:10:21,621 --> 00:10:24,707
It contains the names and photos
of all the FBI agents

194
00:10:24,791 --> 00:10:26,584
currently active in Japan.

195
00:10:26,709 --> 00:10:28,419
[Penber] But-- This… This is…

196
00:10:30,088 --> 00:10:33,007
[Light] Now, one by one
you’re going to look at each photo,

197
00:10:33,133 --> 00:10:35,552
and then write that agent's name
in the space provided.

198
00:10:35,718 --> 00:10:37,554
You're going to do this for each agent.

199
00:10:39,139 --> 00:10:40,765
[Penber] It doesn't make sense.

200
00:10:41,099 --> 00:10:43,768
If he's got the names already
why use me?

201
00:10:44,519 --> 00:10:46,312
What's he planning to do with them?

202
00:10:49,691 --> 00:10:51,192
[Light] Good. Looks like you're done.

203
00:10:51,401 --> 00:10:53,361
Now, put the transceiver
and all the papers

204
00:10:53,486 --> 00:10:55,029
back into the original envelope

205
00:10:55,113 --> 00:10:57,198
and place them on the rack
directly above your head.

206
00:10:57,782 --> 00:10:59,826
After that,
you're going to stay in your seat

207
00:10:59,909 --> 00:11:02,245
and ride the train
for at least another 30 minutes.

208
00:11:02,370 --> 00:11:04,789
When you are absolutely certain
that nobody will notice

209
00:11:04,873 --> 00:11:07,875
you leaving without the envelope,
you can get off of the train.

210
00:11:12,255 --> 00:11:13,923
[Penber] I know that voice.

211
00:11:14,591 --> 00:11:17,468
Why on earth can't I remember
who it belongs to?

212
00:11:26,436 --> 00:11:28,479
Kira… who are you?

213
00:11:30,356 --> 00:11:31,524
[gasps]

214
00:11:31,941 --> 00:11:33,735
[loud heartbeat]

215
00:11:35,111 --> 00:11:37,280
[grunting]

216
00:11:39,115 --> 00:11:41,034
[gasping, groaning]

217
00:11:42,202 --> 00:11:43,411
[train doors hiss]

218
00:11:45,830 --> 00:11:47,040
[groans]

219
00:11:48,249 --> 00:11:50,293
Light… Yagami…

220
00:11:51,711 --> 00:11:53,880
Farewell, Raye Penber.

221
00:12:01,429 --> 00:12:05,475
Raye Penber wrote all of those names
on pages taken from the Death Note.

222
00:12:06,059 --> 00:12:07,143
Ironic.

223
00:12:07,310 --> 00:12:08,478
Without even realizing it,

224
00:12:08,603 --> 00:12:11,689
he was actually signing a death warrant
for all of his colleagues.

225
00:12:12,065 --> 00:12:13,316
As for Penber's boss…

226
00:12:13,441 --> 00:12:17,278
he died of a heart attack
after sending all of his agents a file.

227
00:12:17,445 --> 00:12:19,739
And the other 11 investigators…
[chuckles lightly]

228
00:12:20,198 --> 00:12:24,077
…they all died of heart attacks
after receiving the same file.

229
00:12:44,555 --> 00:12:47,725
[Watari] L… You have a call
from the Director of the FBI.

230
00:12:49,852 --> 00:12:50,937
[FBI Director] It's me.

231
00:12:51,104 --> 00:12:53,606
I've got a report
in front of me right now stating

232
00:12:53,773 --> 00:12:56,109
that all of our agents in Japan
are dead.

233
00:12:56,943 --> 00:12:58,903
All 12 died of heart attacks.

234
00:12:59,279 --> 00:13:01,864
I can only assume
that Kira is behind this.

235
00:13:02,573 --> 00:13:04,117
Look, I'm sorry, but…

236
00:13:04,617 --> 00:13:06,035
It's already decided.

237
00:13:06,202 --> 00:13:08,371
We're calling off our investigation.

238
00:13:09,038 --> 00:13:10,164
[beeping]

239
00:13:10,331 --> 00:13:12,500
[Watari] I have Chief Yagami on the line.

240
00:13:12,834 --> 00:13:15,878
[Yagami] L, I've just got off the phone
with the Director of the FBI.

241
00:13:17,005 --> 00:13:18,089
According to him,

242
00:13:18,214 --> 00:13:20,675
it seems that you arranged for the FBI
to come to Japan

243
00:13:20,842 --> 00:13:24,053
and investigate everyone here
associated with the task force.

244
00:13:24,846 --> 00:13:26,139
[L] Yes, I did.

245
00:13:26,306 --> 00:13:27,890
[Yagami] So, how do you explain this?

246
00:13:28,016 --> 00:13:30,560
Are we now suspects
in our own investigation?

247
00:13:31,227 --> 00:13:34,939
[L] I felt that it was necessary
to uncover Kira's identity.

248
00:13:35,148 --> 00:13:36,733
[Yagami] I cannot accept that.

249
00:13:36,816 --> 00:13:39,068
I find it unbelievable
that you would spy on us,

250
00:13:39,360 --> 00:13:41,738
the very people working with you
on this case.

251
00:13:42,030 --> 00:13:43,072
Hear that?

252
00:13:43,156 --> 00:13:45,575
Well, I knew all along
we couldn't trust that guy.

253
00:13:45,700 --> 00:13:48,828
More importantly,
Kira killed those FBI agents, didn't he?

254
00:13:48,995 --> 00:13:51,247
It's obvious he'll kill anyone
who gets in his way.

255
00:13:51,414 --> 00:13:53,041
Whether they are criminals or not.

256
00:13:53,166 --> 00:13:56,252
So much for his sense of justice.
He's a murderer.

257
00:13:56,419 --> 00:13:57,587
[beeping]

258
00:13:57,754 --> 00:14:01,549
[Watari] We have another victim.
A note was found at the scene.

259
00:14:02,675 --> 00:14:05,636
L, do you know?

260
00:14:05,762 --> 00:14:07,347
Gods of Death…

261
00:14:08,414 --> 00:14:09,457
Huh?

262
00:14:10,767 --> 00:14:12,393
[Light] …love apples.

263
00:14:13,644 --> 00:14:15,063
Damn you, Kira!

264
00:14:19,781 --> 00:14:20,706
[crying]

265
00:14:20,902 --> 00:14:21,986
He's dead.

266
00:14:22,362 --> 00:14:23,613
Raye's dead.

267
00:14:24,572 --> 00:14:25,698
No, he was…

268
00:14:26,348 --> 00:14:28,368
He was murdered by Kira.

269
00:14:32,997 --> 00:14:35,416
[Sayu] Um, so… what's
with the family meeting, Dad?

270
00:14:36,292 --> 00:14:39,045
I figured you're going
to find out sooner or later.

271
00:14:39,212 --> 00:14:40,963
So, I might as well tell you now.

272
00:14:41,381 --> 00:14:42,882
I don't want you to be alarmed.

273
00:14:42,965 --> 00:14:45,051
I'm sure you've heard
of this Kira investigation.

274
00:14:45,176 --> 00:14:46,844
Well, I am currently in charge of it.

275
00:14:46,928 --> 00:14:48,388
What? Are you serious?

276
00:14:48,596 --> 00:14:51,474
That's totally awesome, Dad.
You're the best cop ever.

277
00:14:51,599 --> 00:14:53,726
[Yagami] That's not quite the point
I'm trying to make.

278
00:14:53,810 --> 00:14:54,685
Oh?

279
00:14:56,187 --> 00:14:57,480
You see, the truth is…

280
00:14:57,647 --> 00:15:02,610
the FBI sent 12 of their agents to Japan
to assist us in finding Kira.

281
00:15:02,902 --> 00:15:04,654
And all of them… died yesterday.

282
00:15:04,821 --> 00:15:07,657
-Does that mean they were killed by Kira?
-What?!

283
00:15:07,907 --> 00:15:09,117
What I'm saying is

284
00:15:09,200 --> 00:15:11,494
there's a chance that Kira
will actually try to kill

285
00:15:11,577 --> 00:15:12,954
anyone who comes after him.

286
00:15:13,079 --> 00:15:14,497
His crimes are ruthless

287
00:15:14,580 --> 00:15:16,499
and more frightening
than anything we've seen.

288
00:15:16,582 --> 00:15:18,543
Many detectives have already quit.

289
00:15:18,835 --> 00:15:20,378
Dad, you should quit too!

290
00:15:20,586 --> 00:15:23,089
I don't want you to die!
What if he gets you?

291
00:15:23,172 --> 00:15:24,257
[Sachiko] That's right.

292
00:15:24,340 --> 00:15:26,426
Your life is so much more important
than some job.

293
00:15:26,551 --> 00:15:27,552
I can't.

294
00:15:27,635 --> 00:15:30,179
I could never forgive myself
if I walked away from this.

295
00:15:30,513 --> 00:15:32,849
I will not sit back and let evil triumph.

296
00:15:33,307 --> 00:15:34,851
But, Dad, you…

297
00:15:35,184 --> 00:15:36,394
Please, dear…

298
00:15:37,854 --> 00:15:39,981
I think it's honorable of you, Dad.

299
00:15:40,148 --> 00:15:42,608
I'm proud to be able
to call you my father.

300
00:15:43,317 --> 00:15:46,863
And if anything should ever happen to you,
I'm going to find Kira

301
00:15:47,613 --> 00:15:49,532
and make sure he gets executed.

302
00:15:51,075 --> 00:15:52,118
[door closes]

303
00:15:55,079 --> 00:15:57,582
[Yagami] We now know
that Kira doesn't just target criminals.

304
00:15:57,707 --> 00:15:59,667
He'll kill anyone who opposes him.

305
00:15:59,792 --> 00:16:02,753
It's quite possible
that we may all be killed by Kira.

306
00:16:03,629 --> 00:16:05,089
Think of your own lives,

307
00:16:05,298 --> 00:16:08,426
your families, and all the others
you'd be leaving behind.

308
00:16:08,843 --> 00:16:10,970
If anyone wants
to leave this investigation,

309
00:16:11,345 --> 00:16:12,221
now is the time.

310
00:16:12,930 --> 00:16:15,057
You won't be demoted
if you choose not to stay.

311
00:16:15,266 --> 00:16:16,642
You have my word.

312
00:16:17,977 --> 00:16:21,147
But if you're not absolutely sure
then we don't need you.

313
00:16:21,314 --> 00:16:23,149
You have to be willing
to fight against him,

314
00:16:23,232 --> 00:16:25,735
even if that means
making the ultimate sacrifice.

315
00:16:26,402 --> 00:16:27,278
That is all.

316
00:16:28,404 --> 00:16:30,406
[officer 1] So… what are you gonna do?

317
00:16:30,531 --> 00:16:31,782
[officer 2] I'm not sure.

318
00:16:32,575 --> 00:16:35,620
[driver] Oh, yeah. That' him, all right.
There's no doubt about it.

319
00:16:35,745 --> 00:16:37,705
I remember him
because he told us to get down.

320
00:16:37,955 --> 00:16:40,750
But I don't really remember
any of the other passengers.

321
00:16:41,667 --> 00:16:42,710
[Naomi] I see.

322
00:16:43,211 --> 00:16:46,088
Well, thanks for talking with me, anyway.
I appreciate it.

323
00:16:49,759 --> 00:16:51,260
It's a bit of a long shot.

324
00:16:51,552 --> 00:16:53,095
But if what I'm thinking is right…

325
00:16:53,429 --> 00:16:56,140
Kira could have been
one of the passengers on the bus that day.

326
00:16:56,766 --> 00:16:58,184
And if that is the case,

327
00:16:58,309 --> 00:17:01,354
then I know that he is close enough
to use this bus route.

328
00:17:01,479 --> 00:17:03,397
SERIAL MURDER
SPECIAL INVESTIGATIONS HQ

329
00:17:09,654 --> 00:17:11,072
Five men, huh?

330
00:17:11,531 --> 00:17:13,407
Well, six including myself.

331
00:17:13,616 --> 00:17:15,159
Still, I'm grateful to see

332
00:17:15,284 --> 00:17:19,121
that there's as many as five of you
willing to risk your lives to face evil.

333
00:17:19,539 --> 00:17:22,875
[L] The fact that you've chosen to stay
means you have a strong sense of justice.

334
00:17:23,042 --> 00:17:24,835
-I trust all of you.
-Huh?

335
00:17:25,461 --> 00:17:27,463
Hol-- Hold on a second.

336
00:17:27,588 --> 00:17:29,966
L just said
that he's decided to trust us now.

337
00:17:30,424 --> 00:17:32,969
But honestly, what reason
do we have to trust him?

338
00:17:33,427 --> 00:17:36,722
Look, L, all of us have agreed
to put our lives at risk

339
00:17:36,889 --> 00:17:38,140
to bring Kira to justice.

340
00:17:38,558 --> 00:17:40,601
So, I hope you understand
what this means.

341
00:17:40,685 --> 00:17:42,812
We're really sticking our necks out here.

342
00:17:42,895 --> 00:17:45,022
[Aizawa] But you never have to
show your face, do you?

343
00:17:45,231 --> 00:17:46,691
You just give the orders.

344
00:17:47,066 --> 00:17:49,318
I don't see how you can expect us
to work alongside you

345
00:17:49,485 --> 00:17:50,653
under those conditions.

346
00:17:54,073 --> 00:17:54,949
L.

347
00:17:55,491 --> 00:17:58,244
If all of us are going to work together
on this investigation,

348
00:17:58,452 --> 00:18:01,664
and if you truly meant what you said
about trusting the six of us,

349
00:18:01,956 --> 00:18:04,417
could you come here,
so we can all meet in person?

350
00:18:07,169 --> 00:18:09,046
[L] The thought had
already crossed my mind.

351
00:18:09,213 --> 00:18:12,091
After all, I did say
that I trusted all of you.

352
00:18:17,597 --> 00:18:18,764
[gasping]

353
00:18:19,724 --> 00:18:22,602
Please, keep what is about to happen
a secret between the eight of us.

354
00:18:22,685 --> 00:18:25,646
I would like to meet the six of you
whom I trust as soon as possible.

355
00:18:27,940 --> 00:18:31,569
Before that, I want you all to go
outside of the police building

356
00:18:31,736 --> 00:18:34,363
and decide once more
if you trust me or not.

357
00:18:34,488 --> 00:18:36,490
NATIONAL POLICE AGENCY AND
NATIONAL PUBLIC SAFETY COMMISSION

358
00:18:36,574 --> 00:18:38,951
[Ukita] Why is he seeking our help now?
There's only six of us.

359
00:18:39,160 --> 00:18:42,246
He solved all of these difficult cases
by himself in the past.

360
00:18:42,371 --> 00:18:43,831
So, what makes this one so different?

361
00:18:43,998 --> 00:18:45,958
They way L's been
conducting things so far,

362
00:18:46,125 --> 00:18:49,420
odds are he's gonna send a stand-in
or a proxy of some kind to meet us,

363
00:18:49,587 --> 00:18:50,880
instead of coming himself.

364
00:18:51,088 --> 00:18:52,715
It's not like we'd ever know.

365
00:18:52,882 --> 00:18:54,300
A proxy, huh?

366
00:18:54,675 --> 00:18:55,926
Well, it is possible.

367
00:18:56,260 --> 00:18:58,471
[Matsuda] I believe L.
I think we can trust him.

368
00:18:58,638 --> 00:18:59,639
And besides,

369
00:18:59,805 --> 00:19:02,892
I don't really see how we can
solve this case without his help.

370
00:19:03,309 --> 00:19:04,310
I agree.

371
00:19:05,561 --> 00:19:08,564
From the beginning
he's been very upfront about the fact

372
00:19:08,731 --> 00:19:11,233
that he'd need the help of the police
on this case.

373
00:19:11,776 --> 00:19:14,236
Perhaps we should think of it like…

374
00:19:14,445 --> 00:19:17,156
he's been waiting for this to happen
all along.

375
00:19:17,782 --> 00:19:19,367
Why would he do something like that?

376
00:19:19,533 --> 00:19:21,535
There were a number of people
on the task force

377
00:19:21,619 --> 00:19:24,538
who distrusted L
before this investigation began.

378
00:19:24,747 --> 00:19:25,956
And once we got started,

379
00:19:26,040 --> 00:19:28,501
we had detectives
resigning left and right.

380
00:19:28,584 --> 00:19:31,504
Following that
classified information was leaked.

381
00:19:31,629 --> 00:19:33,798
So, I'm not surprised
that he didn't trust us.

382
00:19:33,964 --> 00:19:36,634
In other words, he was waiting
for the task force to get narrowed down

383
00:19:36,717 --> 00:19:38,719
to only those investigators
he could trust.

384
00:19:38,844 --> 00:19:39,804
And to do that,

385
00:19:39,929 --> 00:19:42,640
he needed to weed out anyone
who wasn't totally committed.

386
00:19:42,973 --> 00:19:43,849
[Yagami] Hmm…

387
00:19:44,266 --> 00:19:45,226
[grunts]

388
00:19:45,893 --> 00:19:48,479
If we're working with that guy,
I'm leaving the task force.

389
00:19:48,646 --> 00:19:49,730
You don't have to worry.

390
00:19:49,897 --> 00:19:53,109
I won't try to follow you,
I'm not interested in finding L.

391
00:19:56,570 --> 00:19:57,863
Well, I think we can trust L,

392
00:19:58,030 --> 00:20:00,658
so I'd be willing to cooperate with him
on this investigation.

393
00:20:00,866 --> 00:20:01,867
Count me in.

394
00:20:06,330 --> 00:20:09,375
[L] I am staying in a suite
at the Teito Hotel at the moment.

395
00:20:09,500 --> 00:20:11,752
But I'll be switching hotels
every few days

396
00:20:11,877 --> 00:20:13,045
from this point on.

397
00:20:13,295 --> 00:20:15,965
I want you to think of these hotel rooms
as the de facto

398
00:20:16,132 --> 00:20:17,967
headquarters of this investigation.

399
00:20:18,134 --> 00:20:19,051
[elevator dings]

400
00:20:19,135 --> 00:20:21,095
[L] If this arrangement
is acceptable to all of you,

401
00:20:21,178 --> 00:20:22,263
then split into two groups

402
00:20:22,596 --> 00:20:25,933
and stagger your arrival,
so you come 30 minutes apart.

403
00:20:26,517 --> 00:20:29,687
Please, arrange it
so you're all here at midnight.

404
00:20:33,190 --> 00:20:34,191
Kira…

405
00:20:34,358 --> 00:20:37,069
it seems we're getting
closer to each other in equal steps.

406
00:20:37,820 --> 00:20:40,406
It's only a matter of time
before we collide.

407
00:20:41,282 --> 00:20:42,283
So be it.

408
00:20:42,616 --> 00:20:44,577
I'm ready to show my face.

409
00:20:44,952 --> 00:20:47,621
I'll make my first public appearance as L.

410
00:20:48,080 --> 00:20:51,041
If you ever manage to find out
about these secret meetings,

411
00:20:51,167 --> 00:20:53,836
I'm sure you'd feel compelled to move in.

412
00:20:54,462 --> 00:20:56,213
That's what I'm counting on.

413
00:20:58,466 --> 00:21:00,885
[Light] I've been quite active
over these last few days.

414
00:21:01,635 --> 00:21:04,138
Think carefully.
Was there anything I missed?

415
00:21:04,472 --> 00:21:08,226
What comes next?
There are endless possibilities.

416
00:21:09,310 --> 00:21:13,147
The real battle
is only just beginning now.

417
00:21:21,405 --> 00:21:22,490
[L] It's unlocked.

418
00:21:22,698 --> 00:21:24,617
Please, let yourselves in.

419
00:21:24,784 --> 00:21:26,035
[Yagami] Hmm.

420
00:21:30,247 --> 00:21:36,253
TO BE CONTINUED

421
00:21:41,759 --> 00:21:44,720
[music playing]
